"{\"description\":\"Assistant Level Crossing Manager job vacancy in Machynlleth, GB\",\"howToApply\":\"Salary: \\nï¿½28,000\\nClosing date: 17th November 2023 - Late applications will not be accepted. \\nClick apply now to apply. \\nDrugs and Alcohol Standard:\\nOur Drugs and Alcohol Standard is changing as of 16.01.2023. All prospective candidates who have not been offered a conditional role by 16.01.2023 will be required to undergo and pass a drugs and alcohol test. Your application will be rescinded if you record a positive test. All positive drugs and alcohol test results for prospective candidates will be securely held on Sentinel database and a 5 year suspension from applying for a safety critical role, a role which requires PTS certification or a Key Safety role on Network Rail Managed Infrastructure will be enforced.\\nYou can visit Evenbreaks Career Hive for advice on accessibility support if you're unsure of the options available. Should you require any reasonable adjustments/modifications, please add a note to your application.\\nNetwork Rail Benefits - To find out about what benefits we offer, click here\\nAll offers of employment are conditional upon satisfactory completion of pre-employment checks. Click here for more information\\nWe positively embrace flexible working recognising that employees may wish to balance work and family/home life.\\nIn Wales and Western region, you will have the opportunity to join PROUD, o r reward and recognition scheme where you can say thanks and recognise colleagues across the region who have demonstrated outstanding values and behaviours.\\nAt Network Rail we promote a diverse and inclusive organisation. We are working in conjunction with the Cultural Fusion team to support black, Asian and minority ethnic colleagues. If you would like support with your application or interview please contact Wales&WesternCulturalFusion@networkrail.co.uk or visit the connect page: Wales and Western Cultural Fusion (sharepoint.com). For all other support please contact your HR Business Partner\",\"aboutTheRole\":{\"essential\":[\"Proven excellent written and verbal communication\",\"Demonstrable excellent interpersonal skills\",\"Proven analytical awareness and attention to detail\",\"Successful experience in planning and organisation\",\"Proven time management skills\",\"Able and willing to drive vehicles as required by business need\",\"Computer literate in basic IT packages\"],\"desirable\":[\"Understanding of level crossings\",\"Attained a Health & Safety qualification\",\"Experience of working in a safety critical environment\"],\"keyAccountabilities\":[\"AssistLCMs with pre and post site visit preparation, including but not limited to arranging joint site visit with stakeholders, corresponding with authorised users and documenting responses, interrogating local authority planning websites, environment websites, and internal systems (GeoRINM, DST), provide asset condition data including outstanding faults, deploy census cameras etc. Undertake level crossing inspection, faulting and undertaking minor maintenance (including cameras, cleaning of signs, minor repairs and vegetation management around the approaches and access area of level crossings); accurately report all work completed/not completed and check that work not completed is faulted. Support LCMs with analysing, documenting, and tracking trend changes from census camera footage. Raising significant changes, deliberate acts of misuse and visible trends in usage with the LCMs and support with any follow-up actions. Assist LCMs with preparation of narrative risk assessments as required, including analysing census camera data, and chasing up information from stakeholders. Work with LCMs to prepare and deliver Safety Awareness events working closely with community safety managers, Train Operating Companies (TOCs) /FreightOperating Companies (FOCs) and British Transport Police (BTP) in the planning and delivery of events. Assist LCMs in the preparation of and attendance at Road Rail Partnership Group meetings, taking minutes and actions as required. Work with stakeholders on behalf of LCMs to manage outputs from meetings, progress fault rectification and updates to systems. Support LCM team by tracking completed Fatality and Weighted Injuries (FWI) reduction activity and updates periodically by keeping the Benefit Report up to date. Support LCMs team with compliance, including but not limited to maintaining incident database, monitoring trends and trigger points, preparation of joint long-term strategy documents, responses to planning applications, maintaining level crossing files etc. Assist LCMs team with projects including signal renewals and timetable change.\"]}}"